7	<p><br/></p>	<p>The Museum at the Xanana Gusmão Reading Room is housed within the magnificent Portuguese colonial building that invites visitors in to the front of our compound. The museum contains permanent/semi-permanent exhibitions, including memorabilia, personal gifts and information on/from Xanana Gusmão. The museum also serves as a space for local artists to display their works for the public. Our museum is an opportunity for the joy of art to be shared and admired in Timor-Leste and is also an opportunity for knowledge to be shared. You may view more about our temporary and permanent exhibitions below. </p>		<p>Muzeu iha Sala Leitura Xanana Gusmão koloka iha edifisiu furak husi tempu kolonial Portuguese nian hatuur iha parte oin ne’ebé mak atrai ema sira atu mai vizita . Iha muzeu laran hatudu espozisaun permanente/semi permanente, inklui rekordasaun, prezente pesoal no informasaun konaba Xanana Gusmão. Muzeu ne'e mos oferese espasu ba artista lokal atu hatudu sira-nia objetu arte nian ba públiku. Ami-nia muzeu fo oportunidade ksolok wain no atu selebra arte hamutuk iha Timor Leste nune'e mos sai hanesan oportunidade ida hodi fahe matenek ba malu. Ita-boot bele haree buat barak tan konaba ami-nia espozisaun temporariu no permananente iha okos.</p>
